❓ QUESTION: Quelle base de données utilisez-vous?

✅ RÉPONSE: MySQL 🐬

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

📋 CONFIGURATION DÉTAILLÉE:

   Type:              MySQL
   Hôte:              127.0.0.1 (localhost)
   Port:              3306 (port standard)
   Nom de la BD:      ne_don_solar_db
   Utilisateur:       root
   Mot de passe:      (aucun/vide)

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

📄 FICHIER DE CONFIGURATION:

   Fichier: .env

   ```
   DB_CONNECTION=mysql
   DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
   DB_PORT=3306
   DB_DATABASE=ne_don_solar_db
   DB_USERNAME=root
   DB_PASSWORD=
   ```

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

🔗 COMMENT ACCÉDER?

   Option 1 - phpMyAdmin (Interface Web):
   http://localhost/phpmyadmin
   User: root
   Password: (vide)

   Option 2 - Ligne de Commande:
   mysql -u root ne_don_solar_db

   Option 3 - Laravel Tinker:
   php artisan tinker
   >>> User::all()
   >>> Formation::all()

   Option 4 - Outils GUI:
   • DBeaver
   • Sequel Pro
   • Navicat
   • MySQL Workbench

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

📊 TABLES PRINCIPALES:

   Authentification:
   • users ........................... Utilisateurs
   • password_resets ................. Réinitialisation

   Métier (Formations):
   • formations ...................... Formations
   • formations_inscriptions ......... Inscriptions
   • classrooms ...................... Salles de classe
   • students ........................ Étudiants

   Installations Solaires:
   • installations ................... Installations
   • devis ........................... Devis
   • orders .......................... Commandes

   Système:
   • log_activites ................... Logs d'activités
   • notifications ................... Notifications
   • settings ........................ Paramètres

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

✅ UTILISATEURS TEST EN BD:

   Après "php artisan users:create-test":

   ID | Email                  | Role        | Password
   ---|------------------------|-------------|----------
   1  | enseignant@test.com    | enseignant  | password
   2  | admin@test.com         | admin       | password

════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

🚀 COMMANDES UTILES:

   Vérifier la connexion:
   php artisan db

   Voir toutes les tables:
   php artisan tinker
   >>> DB::select('SHOW TABLES')

   Exécuter les migrations:
   php artisan migrate

   Ajouter des données:
   php artisan db:seed

   Réinitialiser:
   php artisan migrate:refresh --seed

